## Risk Assessment Conclusion

The risk assessment identified several security weaknesses related to outdated communication protocols, insufficient encryption practices, insecure remote access configurations,
and limited monitoring capabilities within the FinSecure infrastructure. The most critical risks involve the protection of sensitive financial data and administrative access to
internal systems. If exploited, these vulnerabilities could allow attackers to gain unauthorized access to confidential information, compromise internal systems, or disrupt business
operations. Implementing stronger encryption standards, improving access control mechanisms, securing remote access services, and deploying centralized monitoring capabilities would

